RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUN AUNTIE T RUN broke in and bumped rival at the start, pressed leader along the rail on the backstretch, ceded to quicker rival on the turn, eased out around rival on the turn, and launched bid three wide, dueled with fellow rallying rival and proved best late under a drive. AM YISRAEL CHAI stalked pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, launched bid along the inside on the turn and dueled with rival final sixteenth to come up second best. COUSIN NIECEY stalked pace along the inside on the backstretch, continued to save ground on the turn and launched a mild rally along the rail. WETHERLY bit slow and bumped by outside rival at the start, settled off the pace and well off the rail on the backstretch, continued on the scenic route on the turn and into the lane in the five path, kept on willingly to pass some rivals. LIBERTY LIBERTY stalked pace off the rail on the backstretch, continued off the rail on the turn and lacked needed punch in the lane to make an impact. SHEILA'S CHARLIE away well, led two wide on the backstretch, manage to clear rival on the turn, opened up into the stretch, quickly began to shorten stride approaching the sixteenth pole and stopped to a crawl. MIGHTY BOISTEROUS settled off the and on the rail on the backstretch, continued to save ground on the turn, attempted to rally in the four path, but lacked needed kick to improve. MY BELLA CHICK bumped by outside rival and steadied at the start, dropped well back after the trouble start, stayed off the rail on the turn, went widest in the stretch and did make up ground but never threatened.
